
/*
 * // This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to use the [add] slot to append nodes to a specified location in a node structure. The [get-nodes] slot retrieves nodes from a specific path and the [add] slot appends these nodes to the destination specified in its expression. This is useful for dynamically modifying node structures by adding new content at runtime.
 * // 
 * // 1. [add] - Appends nodes to the specified location in the node structure.
 * // 2. [get-nodes] - Retrieves nodes from the specified path in the node structure.
 */
add:x:@.content
   get-nodes:x:@html2lambda/*/html/*/body/**/main/*
